DeltaNet layer — inference — one token

Input: x (hidden state), X (residual accumulator)
Constants: D (hidden dimension), gamma (learned weight per norm)


PRIMITIVES
==========

Every operation is a multiply, add, divide, or function.
The operand decides what it does.

  *           multiply by self (square)
  * -1        multiply by -1 (negate)
  * gamma     multiply by learned weight (scale)
  +           sum all elements (reduction)
  + 1         add scalar 1
  /           divide by another value
  / D         divide by constant
  1 /         reciprocal (1 / x)
  exp         e to the x
  log         natural log
  sqrt        square root
  project     matrix-vector multiply (learned weights)
  delta-update  state recurrence
  matvec      matrix-vector multiply (state @ query)


COMPOSITES
==========

These are not primitives. They are names for sequences of primitives.

  sigmoid   = * -1, exp, + 1, 1 /
  silu      = * -1, exp, + 1, 1 /, *
  softplus  = exp, + 1, log
  normalise = *, +, / D, sqrt, /, * gamma
  l2norm    = *, +, sqrt, /


FULL DECOMPOSITION — 66 STEPS
==============================

RMSNorm on input hidden state

 1  *                square each element
 2  +                sum all squares
 3  / D              mean of squares
 4  sqrt             root mean square
 5  /                x / rms
 6  * gamma          scale by learned weight

 7  project          Q projection
 8  project          K projection
 9  project          V projection

L2-norm on K (after projection, before delta-update)

10  *                square each element of K
11  +                sum all squares
12  sqrt             sqrt(sum)
13  /                K / sqrt(sum)    =  L2-norm(K)

SiLU on Q

14  * -1             -Q
15  exp              e^(-Q)
16  + 1              1 + e^(-Q)
17  1 /              1 / (1 + e^(-Q))  =  sigmoid(Q)
18  *                Q * sigmoid(Q)    =  SiLU(Q)

L2-norm on Q (after SiLU, before matvec)

19  *                square each element of Q
20  +                sum all squares
21  sqrt             sqrt(sum)
22  /                Q / sqrt(sum)    =  L2-norm(Q)

Sigmoid on beta

23  * -1             -beta
24  exp              e^(-beta)
25  + 1              1 + e^(-beta)
26  1 /              1 / (1 + e^(-beta))  =  sigmoid(beta)

Decay gate (GatedDeltaNet)
  a_proj = in_proj_a @ x  (already computed as part of in_proj)
  g = -exp(A_log) * softplus(a_proj + dt_bias)
  decay = exp(g)

27  +                t = a_proj + dt_bias
28  exp              exp(t)
29  + 1              1 + exp(t)
30  log              log(1 + exp(t))      =  softplus(t)
31  exp              exp(A_log)
32  * -1             -exp(A_log)
33  *                g = -exp(A_log) * softplus(t)
34  exp              decay = exp(g)

Delta rule (with decay)

35  delta-update     S = decay * S + beta * (V ⊗ K - S · (K ⊗ K))
36  matvec           output = S @ Q

Output gate (g_proj)

37  project          z = W_z @ x  (output gate projection)
38  * -1             -z
39  exp              e^(-z)
40  + 1              1 + e^(-z)
41  1 /              1 / (1 + e^(-z))  =  sigmoid(z)
42  *                output * sigmoid(z)  (gate multiply)

RMSNorm on gated output

43  *                square each element
44  +                sum all squares
45  / D              mean of squares
46  sqrt             root mean square
47  /                output / rms
48  * gamma          scale by learned weight

49  project          output projection
50  +                residual into X

RMSNorm on X (MLP input)

51  *                square each element
52  +                sum all squares
53  / D              mean of squares
54  sqrt             root mean square
55  /                X / rms
56  * gamma          scale by learned weight

57  project          gate projection
58  project          up projection

SiLU on gate

59  * -1             -gate
60  exp              e^(-gate)
61  + 1              1 + e^(-gate)
62  1 /              1 / (1 + e^(-gate))  =  sigmoid(gate)
63  *                gate * sigmoid(gate) =  SiLU(gate)

64  *                gate * up  (element-wise multiply)

65  project          down projection
66  +                residual into X
